# Database Standards

Schema changes:
- All schema changes must be migration based — never modify schema manually
- One migration per logical change; never bundle unrelated schema changes
- Migrations live in `backend/migrations/` (Alembic or equivalent)
- DB session/engine setup belongs in `backend/app/db/` only

ORM and queries:
- ORM models belong only in `models.py` per module
- All SQL and ORM queries belong only in `repository.py` — never in service or router layers
- Parameterized queries only — never string-concatenated SQL
- No N+1 queries — use joinedload() or selectinload() explicitly
- Never fetch unbounded datasets — all list queries must be paginated
- Select explicit columns — avoid SELECT *
- Index foreign keys and all columns used in WHERE or ORDER BY

Naming:
- Tables: `snake_case`, plural (`users`, `report_entries`)
- Columns: `snake_case`
- Foreign keys: `<referenced_table_singular>_id`

Migrations:
- Include both upgrade and downgrade paths when feasible
- Name migrations descriptively: `add_users_email_index`, not `migration_003`
- Review migration SQL for locking impact on large tables before merge
